    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="man_ej.00093_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Detroit</name>
                    <date when="1880-07-19">July 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1880</date>
                    <name type="place">169 East Elisabeth <choice><abbr>St</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></name>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Mr W Whitman</salute>
                <salute>Dear Friend&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I was ever so sorry today to see by the Paper you sent me,<ptr target="n1017"/> that you were ill I hope
                this will find you ever so much better&#8212;<choice><orig>Cant</orig><reg>Can't</reg></choice> you let me know that you are I
                <choice><orig>dont</orig><reg>don't</reg></choice> want you to go home without visiting Detroit, I would like to have you make
                your visit a little late, I will tell you why&#8212;My husband and a son in law
                are making a trip around the Lakes to Chicago and back&#8212;and my son in law
                Lewis T Ives&#8212;with his
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="man_ej.00095_large.jpg"
                    type="verso"/>
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="man_ej.00203_large.jpg"
                    type="verso"/>son<ptr target="man.00038_n1"/> are at Pittsfield Mass they are both Artists, Father and son&#8212;the latter just sixteen years of age&#8212;but of great promise&#8212;I
                know that my son Lewis would be so glad to meet you. You will remember that he was
                the one who rescued your Leaves of Grass for me, and brought it from
                England Did you get the story of the Book?</p>

            <p>If you do not feel well enough to answer my questions&#8212;<choice><orig>wont</orig><reg>won't</reg></choice> some friend do it
                for me&#8212;and please let me be assured of a visit from you before you
                return</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>I am very truly</salute>
                <salute>Yours obliged</salute>
                <signed>Elisa S Leggett.</signed>
            </closer><pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="man_ej.00204_large.jpg"
                type="verso"/>
        </body>
